refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
booloutput_reset_rewrite_vars
This function resets the URL rewriter and removes all rewrite variables previously set by the output_add_rewrite_var function.

&reftitle.changelog;







     &Version;
     &Description;





     7.1.0

      Before PHP 7.1.0, rewrite vars set by output_add_rewrite_var
      use the same Session module trans sid output buffer. Since PHP 7.1.0,
      dedicated output buffer is used and output_reset_rewrite_vars
      only removes rewrite vars defined by output_add_rewrite_var.

  &reftitle.examples;



    output_reset_rewrite_vars example


<?php
session_start();
output_add_rewrite_var('var', 'value');

echo '<a href="file.php">link</a>';
ob_flush();

output_reset_rewrite_vars();
echo '<a href="file.php">link</a>';
?>


    &example.outputs;


<a href="file.php?PHPSESSID=xxx&var=value">link</a>
<a href="file.php">link</a>
